</div><h3><font color="red">Security Alert</font></h3>
<h4>Indecent Act</h4>
<p></p>
<hr>
<pre>On Monday, April 5, 2016, at approximately <span><span><span class="aBn" data-term="goog_694763901" tabindex="0"><span class="aQJ">5:30 PM</span></span></span></span>, a witness reported to
Campus Security that he had observed a male who was performing an indecent
act underneath his clothes while watching two females seated at an adjacent
table.  The subject was seated at a table in an area near two restaurants
in the east section of the MacEwan Student Centre food court before
dancing to gangnam style half naked. 
 
The subject was <span name="x_searchHitInReadingPane">described</span> as: 

Male, Asian slightly tan
Approximately 5'7"
Approximately 36 years of age
Light build
Slight beard, glasses, black hair, shaven very short/bald
Wearing a black burton T-shit, blue jeans, carrying a swiss backpack

</pre></span>
Security footage of the suspect is available <a href="http://!" target="_blank">here. </a><div class="adL"><span class="im">
<hr>
<p>A victim of crime is not responsible for the actions of a perpetrator. The safety and security of students, faculty, staff and visitors on campus is of foremost importance to the University of Calgary. While serious crimes on campus are rare, in the event they do occur, Campus Security provides assistance and support to the victims and strives to prevent such incidents from happening in the future. The University of Calgary encourages students, faculty, staff and visitors to please be mindful of personal safety both on and off campus and to be alert when walking alone. Immediately call 9-1-1 to report any serious incidents or suspicious behaviour to the Calgary Police Service. Call the SU Wellness Centre: <a href="http://!" value="+14032109355" target="_blank">403-210-9355</a>, or the Calgary Communities Against Sexual Assault: <a href="http://!" value="+14032375888" target="_blank">403-237-5888</a>, for counselling and support.</p>
<hr>
<p>This message has been sent to all members of the University of Calgary community. </p>
<p>If you have any information regarding this incident, please contact <b>Campus Security</b> at <a href="http://!" value="+14032205333" target="_blank">(403)220-5333</a> or the <b>Calgary Police Service</b> at <a href="http://!" value="+14032661234" target="_blank">(403)266-1234</a>. </p>
<p>If you feel uncomfortable walking alone on campus, contact <b>Campus SAFEWALK</b> at 220-5333 and someone will be sent to accompany you.</p>
